BE IT ENACTED BY THE GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF OHIO:
Section 1. (A) The Support Children's Overall 4
Psychological and Emotional Health (SCOPE) Pilot Program is 5
established in collaboration between the Department of Health 6
and the Department of Behavioral Health. The purpose of the 7
SCOPE Pilot Program is to provide mental health services to 8
individuals eligible for the Program for Children and Youth with 9
Special Health Care Needs under sections 3701.021 to 3701.028 of 10
the Revised Code. 11
(B) The SCOPE Pilot Program shall address mental health 12
conditions that are commonly experienced by children and 13
families managing complex medical issues. The Department of 14
Health and the Department of Behavioral Health shall work 15
collaboratively to initiate and oversee the delivery of mental 16
health services under the Pilot Program, including all of the 17
following: 18
(1) Identifying mental health conditions that warrant 19

