the medication for the treatment of mental health conditions; 26
(3) Establishing criteria for the provision of services 27
under the Pilot Program; 28
(4) Generating a list of providers to provide services 29
under the Pilot Program. 30
(C) The Department of Health shall inform families who are 31
eligible for the Program for Children and Youth with Special 32
Health Care Needs under sections 3701.021 to 3701.028 of the 33
Revised Code about the SCOPE Pilot Program. The Pilot Program 34
shall operate independently from the Program for Children and 35
Youth with Special Health Care Needs. 36
(D) The SCOPE Pilot Program terminates after one year or 37
when funding is exhausted, whichever occurs first. Upon the 38
termination of the Pilot Program, the Department of Health and 39
Department of Behavioral Health jointly shall survey 40
participating families to assess the Pilot Program's 41
effectiveness. 42
